## VI. EVALUATION METHODOLOGY

**Status: simulation in progress.** We are implementing a Python-based CXL fabric simulator (FabricModel, MCTPBus, DCDModel, AttackHarness) to validate ATK-1 through ATK-4 against measured rather than assumed latency and success-rate figures. The bus-latency model will be framed around MCTP-over-PCIe-VDM transport, where sub-microsecond message timing is physically plausible, rather than MCTP-over-SMBus, where standard clock rates (100 kHz–1 MHz) imply transmission times one to three orders of magnitude slower than sub-microsecond. Planned methodology: each attack executed across N randomized trials (victim tenant/port/extent selection, randomized bus latency), recording success rate, mean latency, and standard deviation. *Quantitative results (success rate, latency, LLM workload impact) will be added once the simulator is implemented and executed — see Section X.*

